            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-30 16:23:51" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to show kindness to someone, with the implication of graciousness on the part of the one showing such kindness</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to show kindness</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to manifest graciousness toward</Gloss>
                <Gloss>kindness</Gloss>
                <Gloss>graciousness</Gloss>
                <Gloss>grace</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is important to note that kindness in English indicates an activity in which an individual is kind to someone; it is essentially an event involving a particular quality. The same is true of χάρις in {S:04401504000016}, for this is not a mere gracious disposition, but an expectation of the Lord’s showing kindness.</Comments>
